    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by heightened operational tempo across multiple theaters, with a clear emphasis on deterrence, crisis response, and multilateral security cooperation. The deployment of four carrier strike groups—USS Gerald R. Ford, USS Harry S. Truman, USS Dwight D. Eisenhower, and USS Theodore Roosevelt—demonstrates a strategic focus on maintaining forward presence in both the Indo-Pacific and Atlantic regions, particularly through participation in major exercises like RIMPAC 2026. The Mediterranean remains a critical operational hub, with amphibious ready groups and cruisers actively supporting NATO exercises, reflecting efforts to reinforce regional stability amid geopolitical tensions. ISR activity has intensified, with advanced platforms such as Boeing C-30J and high-altitude reconnaissance systems conducting surveillance over key maritime chokepoints, including the Strait of Hormuz, where recent U.S. actions have disrupted Iranian oil smuggling networks. The data also highlights increased production of stealthy cruise and anti-ship missiles, indicating a shift toward enhancing long-range strike capabilities. Overall, the military posture reflects a commitment to rapid deployment, sustained deterrence, and operational flexibility, with a clear focus on maintaining readiness across global hotspots while strengthening alliances through joint exercises and cooperative security initiatives.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
